<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="350" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1283,1705]" pageId="8" pageNumber="350">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1535,1561]" pageId="8" pageNumber="350">Remarks.</emphasis>
A typical member of the 
<taxonomicName authority="Bezzi, 1920" authorityName="Bezzi" authorityYear="1920" box="[597,1003,1535,1561]" class="Insecta" family="Lonchaeidae" genus="Lonchaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="350" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="impressifrons">
<emphasis box="[597,864,1535,1561]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="350">Lonchaea impressifrons</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bezzi, M." box="[870,1003,1535,1561]" pageId="8" pageNumber="350" pagination="199 - 210" refId="ref10168" refString="Bezzi, M. (1920) Further Notes on the Lonchaeidae (Dipt.), with Descriptions of New Species from Africa and Asia. Bulletin of Entomological Research, 11 (3), 199 - 210. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0007485300044643" type="journal article" year="1920">Bezzi, 1920</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
species group as defined by 
<bibRefCitation author="McAlpine, J. F." pageId="8" pageNumber="350" pagination="1950 - 1951" refId="ref10550" refString="McAlpine, J. F. (1960) Chapter XVI. Diptera (Brachycera): Lonchaeidae. In: Hanstrom, B., Brink, P. &amp; Rudebeck, G. (Eds.), South African animal life. Results of the Lund University Expedition 1950 - 1951. Vol. 7. Almqvist and Wisell, Goteborg, Stockholm, Uppsala pp. 327 - 376." type="book chapter" year="1960">McAlpine (1960)</bibRefCitation>
. With long, stalked cerci and long, asymmetrical pregonites this species is perhaps most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="de Meijere, 1910" authorityName="de Meijere" authorityYear="1910" class="Insecta" family="Lonchaeidae" genus="Lonchaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="350" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minuta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="350">Lonchaea minuta</emphasis>
de Meijere, 1910
</taxonomicName>
known from 
<collectingRegion box="[582,634,1608,1634]" country="Indonesia" name="Jawa Timur" pageId="8" pageNumber="350">Java</collectingRegion>
, the male terminalia of which are illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="McAlpine, J. F." box="[1176,1433,1607,1634]" pageId="8" pageNumber="350" pagination="989 - 1007" refId="ref10715" refString="McAlpine, J. F. (1975) Identities of lance flies (Diptera: Lonchaeidae) described by de Meijere, with notes on related species. The Canadian Entomologist, 107 (9), 989 - 1007. https: // doi. org / 10.4039 / Ent 107989 - 9" type="journal article" year="1975">McAlpine (1975: 991)</bibRefCitation>
. However, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="MacGowan" authorityYear="2021" box="[266,348,1643,1669]" class="Insecta" family="Lonchaeidae" genus="Lonchaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="350" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="efate">
<emphasis box="[266,348,1643,1669]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="350">L. efate</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is clearly distinctive in that the surstyli are longer and it is the left pregonite which is longer rather than the right.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
